  "market_context": "Uptrend preceding the pattern, followed by formation of an ascending triangle with consecutive higher lows and horizontal resistance. Price then broke above resistance with a strong momentum candle.",
  "key_observation": "The analyst identified a real-world ascending triangle formed by consecutive higher lows and near-identical swing highs, culminating in a strong breakout candle above resistance.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Confirmed prior uptrend before the pattern emerged.",
    "Step 2: Identified consecutive higher lows and swing highs at approximately the same level to define the ascending triangle structure.",
    "Step 3: Drew a rising trendline connecting the higher lows and a horizontal line connecting the swing highs.",
    "Step 4: Waited for a strong breakout candle (larger real body than prior candles) above resistance to signal entry.",
    "Step 5: Placed stop loss just below the most recent low inside the triangle.",
    "Step 6: Set target using 1:2 risk-to-reward ratio from entry to stop distance."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price broke above resistance and continued upward without pullback; trade was successful per analyst’s description.",
  "lessons": "Ascending triangles are reliable bullish continuation patterns when formed after an uptrend; breakout entries require strong momentum candles, and stop placement below the last swing low is critical.",
